  2022,"10",/general-conference/2022/10/14renlund,Elder Dale G. Renlund,34,"The scriptures teach that the voice of the Holy Ghost is mild and still, like a whisper—not loud or noisy; it is simple, quiet, and plain; it can be piercing and burning; it affects both mind and heart; it brings peace, joy, and hope—not fear, anxiety, and worry; it invites us to do good—not evil; and it is enlightening and delicious—not mystifying. See1 Kings 19:11–12;Omni 1:25;Alma 32:28;Helaman 5:30–33;3 Nephi 11:3;Moroni 7:16–17;Doctrine and Covenants 6:22–24;8:2–3;9:8–9;11:12–14;85:6; Boyd K. Packer, “The Candle of the Lord,”Ensign, Jan. 1983, 51–56; Russell M. Nelson, “Hear Him,”EnsignorLiahona, May 2020, 88–92; Russell M. Nelson, “Embrace the Future with Faith,”EnsignorLiahona, Nov. 2020, 73–76; Russell M. Nelson, “Revelation for the Church, Revelation for Our Lives,” 93–96."
