  2022,"10",/general-conference/2022/10/54eddy,Elder Mark D. Eddy,40,"SeeDoctrine and Covenants 1:14–18."
  2022,"10",/general-conference/2022/10/54eddy,Elder Mark D. Eddy,41,"Amos 8:11."
  2022,"10",/general-conference/2022/10/54eddy,Elder Mark D. Eddy,42,"SeeAlma 34:6."
  2022,"10",/general-conference/2022/10/54eddy,Elder Mark D. Eddy,43,"SeeJohn 15:10."
  2022,"10",/general-conference/2022/10/54eddy,Elder Mark D. Eddy,44,"SeeMark 5:25–34."
  2022,"10",/general-conference/2022/10/54eddy,Elder Mark D. Eddy,45,"Moroni 7:31."
  2022,"10",/general-conference/2022/10/54eddy,Elder Mark D. Eddy,46,"“There is a better way to prepare, because great faith has a short shelf life. We could decide to persist in studying the words of Christ in the scriptures and the teachings of living prophets. This is what I will do. I will go back to the Book of Mormon and drink deeply and often” (Henry B. Eyring, “Spiritual Preparedness: Start Early and Be Steady,”EnsignorLiahona, Nov. 2005, 39)."
  2022,"10",/general-conference/2022/10/54eddy,Elder Mark D. Eddy,47,"“For me, the reading of the scriptures is not the pursuit of scholarship. Rather, it is a love affair with the word of the Lord and that of his prophets. …"
  2022,"10",/general-conference/2022/10/54eddy,Elder Mark D. Eddy,48,"“I do not concern myself much with reading long commentary volumes designed to enlarge at length upon that which is found in the scriptures. Rather, I prefer to dwell with the source, tasting of the unadulterated waters of the foundation of truth—the word of God as he gave it and as it has been recorded in the books we accept as scripture. Through reading the scriptures, we can gain the assurance of the Spirit that that which we read has come of God for the enlightenment, blessing, and joy of his children” (Gordon B. Hinckley, “Feasting upon the Scriptures,”Ensign, Dec. 1985, 44, 45;Tambuli, June 1986, 2, 4)."
  2022,"10",/general-conference/2022/10/54eddy,Elder Mark D. Eddy,49,"Russell M. Nelson, “The Book of Mormon: What Would Your Life Be Like without It?,”EnsignorLiahona, Nov. 2017, 62–63."
  2022,"10",/general-conference/2022/10/54eddy,Elder Mark D. Eddy,50,"John 1:14."
  2022,"10",/general-conference/2022/10/54eddy,Elder Mark D. Eddy,51,"See1 Nephi 8:30."
  2022,"10",/general-conference/2022/10/54eddy,Elder Mark D. Eddy,52,"“The covenant path is theonlypath that leads to exaltation and eternal life” (Russell M. Nelson, “The Power of Spiritual Momentum,”Liahona, May 2022, 98)."
  2022,"10",/general-conference/2022/10/54eddy,Elder Mark D. Eddy,53,"SeeAlma 5:11–13."
  2022,"10",/general-conference/2022/10/55stevenson,Elder Gary E. Stevenson,4,"Defining moments in life come often and unexpectedly, even when you are still young. Allow me to share a story about a high school student, Kevin, chosen to travel out of state for a student leader event, as told in his own words."
  2022,"10",/general-conference/2022/10/55stevenson,Elder Gary E. Stevenson,5,"“My turn in line came, and the official-looking registration clerk asked for my name. She looked at her list and said, ‘So you’re the young man from Utah.’"
  2022,"10",/general-conference/2022/10/55stevenson,Elder Gary E. Stevenson,6,“‘You mean I’m the only one?’ I asked.
  2022,"10",/general-conference/2022/10/55stevenson,Elder Gary E. Stevenson,7,"“‘Yes, the only one.’ She handed me my name tag with ‘Utah’ printed below my name. As I clipped it on, I felt like I was being branded."
  2022,"10",/general-conference/2022/10/55stevenson,Elder Gary E. Stevenson,8,"“I crowded into the hotel elevator with five other high school students with name tags like mine. ‘Hey, you’re from Utah. Are you a Mormon?’ asked one student."
  2022,"10",/general-conference/2022/10/55stevenson,Elder Gary E. Stevenson,9,"“I felt out of place with all these student leaders from all over the country. ‘Yes,’ I hesitantly admitted."
  2022,"10",/general-conference/2022/10/55stevenson,Elder Gary E. Stevenson,10,"“‘You’re the guys who believe in Joseph Smith, who said he saw angels. You don’t actually believe that, do you?’"
  2022,"10",/general-conference/2022/10/55stevenson,Elder Gary E. Stevenson,11,"“I didn’t know what to say. The students in the elevator were all staring at me. I had just arrived, and already everyone thought I was different. I became a little defensive but then said, ‘I know that Joseph Smith was a prophet of God.’"
  2022,"10",/general-conference/2022/10/55stevenson,Elder Gary E. Stevenson,12,“‘Where had that come from?’ I wondered. I didn’t know I had it in me. But the words felt true.
  2022,"10",/general-conference/2022/10/55stevenson,Elder Gary E. Stevenson,13,"“‘Yeah, I was told that you were all just religious nuts,’ he said."
  2022,"10",/general-conference/2022/10/55stevenson,Elder Gary E. Stevenson,14,"“With that, there was an uncomfortable pause as the elevator door opened. As we gathered our luggage, he walked down the hall laughing."
  2022,"10",/general-conference/2022/10/55stevenson,Elder Gary E. Stevenson,15,"“Then, a voice behind me asked, ‘Hey, don’t Mormons have some sort of another Bible?’"
  2022,"10",/general-conference/2022/10/55stevenson,Elder Gary E. Stevenson,16,"“Oh no. Not again. I turned to see another student who had been in the elevator with me, Christopher."
  2022,"10",/general-conference/2022/10/55stevenson,Elder Gary E. Stevenson,17,"“‘It’s called the Book of Mormon,’ I said, wanting to drop the subject. I picked up my bags and started walking down the hall."
  2022,"10",/general-conference/2022/10/55stevenson,Elder Gary E. Stevenson,18,“‘Is that the book Joseph Smith translated?’ he asked.
  2022,"10",/general-conference/2022/10/55stevenson,Elder Gary E. Stevenson,19,"“‘Yeah, it is,’ I answered. I kept on walking, hoping to avoid embarrassment."
  2022,"10",/general-conference/2022/10/55stevenson,Elder Gary E. Stevenson,20,"“‘Well, do you know how I could get one?’"
  2022,"10",/general-conference/2022/10/55stevenson,Elder Gary E. Stevenson,21,"“A scripture I learned in seminary suddenly came to me. ‘I am not ashamed of the gospel of Jesus Christ.’As this entered my mind, I felt ashamed I had been so embarrassed."
  2022,"10",/general-conference/2022/10/55stevenson,Elder Gary E. Stevenson,22,"“For the rest of the week that scripture wouldn’t leave me. I answered as many questions about the Church as Icould, and I made many friends."
  2022,"10",/general-conference/2022/10/55stevenson,Elder Gary E. Stevenson,23,“I discovered I was proud of my religion.
  2022,"10",/general-conference/2022/10/55stevenson,Elder Gary E. Stevenson,24,"“I gave Christopher a Book of Mormon. He later wrote me, telling me he had invited the missionaries to his home."
  2022,"10",/general-conference/2022/10/55stevenson,Elder Gary E. Stevenson,25,“I learned not to be embarrassed to share my testimony.”
  2022,"10",/general-conference/2022/10/55stevenson,Elder Gary E. Stevenson,26,"I am inspired by Kevin’s courage in sharing his testimony. It is a courage repeated every day by faithful members of the Church throughout the world. As I share my thoughts, I invite you to reflect upon these four questions:"
  2022,"10",/general-conference/2022/10/55stevenson,Elder Gary E. Stevenson,27,Do I know and understand what a testimony is?
  2022,"10",/general-conference/2022/10/55stevenson,Elder Gary E. Stevenson,28,Do I know how to bear my testimony?
  2022,"10",/general-conference/2022/10/55stevenson,Elder Gary E. Stevenson,29,What are the obstacles in sharing my testimony?
  2022,"10",/general-conference/2022/10/55stevenson,Elder Gary E. Stevenson,30,How do I keep my testimony?
  2022,"10",/general-conference/2022/10/55stevenson,Elder Gary E. Stevenson,31,"Your testimony is a most precious possession, often associated with deep spiritual feelings. These feelings are usually communicated quietly and described as a “still small voice.”It is your belief or knowledge of truth given as a spiritual witness through the influence of the Holy Ghost. Acquiring this witness will change what you say and how you act. Key elements of your testimony, confirmed by the Holy Ghost, include:"
  2022,"10",/general-conference/2022/10/55stevenson,Elder Gary E. Stevenson,32,God is your Heavenly Father; you are His child. He loves you.
  2022,"10",/general-conference/2022/10/55stevenson,Elder Gary E. Stevenson,33,Jesus Christ lives. He is the Son of the living God and your Savior and Redeemer.
  2022,"10",/general-conference/2022/10/55stevenson,Elder Gary E. Stevenson,34,Joseph Smith is a prophet of God called to restore the Church of Jesus Christ.
  2022,"10",/general-conference/2022/10/55stevenson,Elder Gary E. Stevenson,35,The Church of Jesus Christ of Latter-day Saints is God’s restored Church on the earth.
  2022,"10",/general-conference/2022/10/55stevenson,Elder Gary E. Stevenson,36,The restored Church of Jesus Christ is led by a living prophet today.
  2022,"10",/general-conference/2022/10/55stevenson,Elder Gary E. Stevenson,37,"You bear your testimony when you share spiritual feelings with others. As a member of the Church, you have opportunities to bear your spoken testimony in formal Church meetings or in less formal, one-on-one conversations with family, friends, and others."
  2022,"10",/general-conference/2022/10/55stevenson,Elder Gary E. Stevenson,38,Another way you share your testimony is through righteous behavior. Your testimony in Jesus Christ isn’t just what you say—it’s who you are.
  2022,"10",/general-conference/2022/10/55stevenson,Elder Gary E. Stevenson,39,"Each time you bear vocal witness or demonstrate through your actions your commitment to follow Jesus Christ, you invite others to “come unto Christ.”"
  2022,"10",/general-conference/2022/10/55stevenson,Elder Gary E. Stevenson,40,"Members of the Church stand as witnesses of God at all times, in all things, and in all places.Opportunities to do this in the digital universe using inspiring content of our own or sharing uplifting content prepared by others are endless. We testify when we love, share, and invite, even online. Your tweets, direct messages, and posts will take on a higher, holier purpose when you also use social media to show how the gospel of Jesus Christ shapes your life."
  2022,"10",/general-conference/2022/10/55stevenson,Elder Gary E. Stevenson,41,"Obstacles to sharing your testimony may include uncertainty about what to say. Matthew Cowley, an early Apostle, shared this experience as he departed on a five-year mission at age 17 to New Zealand:"
  2022,"10",/general-conference/2022/10/55stevenson,Elder Gary E. Stevenson,42,"“I will never forget the prayers of my father the day that I left. I have never heard a more beautiful blessing in all my life. Then his last words to me at the railroad station, ‘My boy, you will go out on that mission; you will study; you will try to prepare your sermons; and sometimes when you are called upon, you will think you are wonderfully prepared, butwhen you stand up, your mind will go completely blank.’ I have had that experience more than once."
  2022,"10",/general-conference/2022/10/55stevenson,Elder Gary E. Stevenson,43,"“I said, ‘What do you do when your mind goes blank?’"
  2022,"10",/general-conference/2022/10/55stevenson,Elder Gary E. Stevenson,44,"“He said, ‘You stand up there and with all the fervor of your soul, you bear witness that Joseph Smith was a prophet of the living God, and thoughts will flood into your mind and words to your mouth … to the heart of everyone who listens.’ And so my mind, being mostly blank during my … mission … , gave me the opportunity to bear testimony to the greatest event in the history of the world since the crucifixion of the Master. Try it sometime, fellows and girls. If you don’t have anything else to say, testify that Joseph Smith was the prophet of God, and the whole history of the Church will flood into your mind.”"
  2022,"10",/general-conference/2022/10/55stevenson,Elder Gary E. Stevenson,45,"Likewise, President Dallin H. Oaks shared, “Some testimonies are better gained on the feet bearing them than on the knees praying for them.”The Spirit bears witness to the speaker and listener alike."
  2022,"10",/general-conference/2022/10/55stevenson,Elder Gary E. Stevenson,46,"Another obstacle, as Kevin’s story emphasized, is fear. As Paul wrote to Timothy:"
  2022,"10",/general-conference/2022/10/55stevenson,Elder Gary E. Stevenson,47,"“God hath not given us the spirit of fear; but of power, and of love. …"
  2022,"10",/general-conference/2022/10/55stevenson,Elder Gary E. Stevenson,48,“Be not thou therefore ashamed of the testimony of our Lord.”
  2022,"10",/general-conference/2022/10/55stevenson,Elder Gary E. Stevenson,49,"Feelings of fear don’t come from the Lord but most often from the adversary. Having faith, as Kevin did, will allow you to overcome these feelings and freely share what is in your heart."
  2022,"10",/general-conference/2022/10/55stevenson,Elder Gary E. Stevenson,50,"I believe a testimony is innate within us, yet, in order to keep it and more fully develop it, Alma taught that we must nourish our testimony with much care.As we do so, “it will get root, and grow up, and bring forth fruit.”Without this, “it withers away.”"
  2022,"10",/general-conference/2022/10/55stevenson,Elder Gary E. Stevenson,51,Each beloved member of the First Presidency has provided us with direction on how to keep a testimony.
  2022,"10",/general-conference/2022/10/55stevenson,Elder Gary E. Stevenson,52,"President Henry B. Eyring lovingly taught us that “feasting on the word of God, heartfelt prayer, and obedience to the Lord’s commandments must be applied evenly and continually for your testimony to grow and prosper.”"
  2022,"10",/general-conference/2022/10/55stevenson,Elder Gary E. Stevenson,53,"President Dallin H. Oaks reminded us that to retain our testimony, “we need to partake of the sacrament each week (seeD&C 59:9) to qualify for the precious promise that we will ‘always have his Spirit to be with [us]’ (D&C 20:77).”"
  2022,"10",/general-conference/2022/10/55stevenson,Elder Gary E. Stevenson,54,"And President Russell M. Nelson kindly counseled recently:"
  2022,"10",/general-conference/2022/10/55stevenson,Elder Gary E. Stevenson,55,"“Feed [your testimony] truth. …"
  2022,"10",/general-conference/2022/10/55stevenson,Elder Gary E. Stevenson,56,“… Nourish yourself in the words of ancient and modern prophets. Ask the Lord to teach you how to hear Him better. Spend more time in the temple and in family history work.
  2022,"10",/general-conference/2022/10/55stevenson,Elder Gary E. Stevenson,57,“… Make your testimony your highest priority.”
  2022,"10",/general-conference/2022/10/55stevenson,Elder Gary E. Stevenson,58,"My beloved brothers and sisters, I promise that as you more fully understand what a testimony is, and as you share it, you will overcome obstacles of uncertainty and fear, enabling you to nurture and keep this most precious possession, your testimony."
  2022,"10",/general-conference/2022/10/55stevenson,Elder Gary E. Stevenson,59,We are blessed to have countless examples of ancient and modern-day prophets who have boldly borne their testimonies.
  2022,"10",/general-conference/2022/10/55stevenson,Elder Gary E. Stevenson,60,"Following Christ’s death, Peter stood and testified:"
  2022,"10",/general-conference/2022/10/55stevenson,Elder Gary E. Stevenson,61,"“Be it known unto you all … that by the name of Jesus Christ of Nazareth, whom ye crucified, whom God raised from the dead, … doth this man stand here before you. …"
  2022,"10",/general-conference/2022/10/55stevenson,Elder Gary E. Stevenson,62,"“… For there is none other name under heaven given among men, whereby we must be saved.”"
  2022,"10",/general-conference/2022/10/55stevenson,Elder Gary E. Stevenson,63,"Amulek, following Alma’s sermon on faith, stated powerfully: “I will testify unto you of myself that these things are true. Behold, I say unto you, that I do know that Christ shall come among the children of men, … and that he shall atone for the sins of the world; for the Lord God hath spoken it.”"
  2022,"10",/general-conference/2022/10/55stevenson,Elder Gary E. Stevenson,64,"Joseph Smith and Sidney Rigdon, upon witnessing a glorious vision of the resurrected Savior, testified:"
  2022,"10",/general-conference/2022/10/55stevenson,Elder Gary E. Stevenson,65,"“And now, after the many testimonies which have been given of him, this is the testimony, last of all, which we give of him: That he lives!"
  2022,"10",/general-conference/2022/10/55stevenson,Elder Gary E. Stevenson,66,"“For we saw him, even on the right hand of God; and we heard the voice bearing record that he is the Only Begotten of the Father.”"
  2022,"10",/general-conference/2022/10/55stevenson,Elder Gary E. Stevenson,67,"Brothers and sisters, I invite you to seek opportunities to bear your testimony in word and in deed. Such an opportunity came to me recently, at the end of a meeting with the mayor of a capital city in South America, in his chambers with a number of his cabinet officials. As we concluded with very cordial feelings, I hesitantly thought I should share my testimony.Following the prompting, I offered a witness that Jesus Christ is the Son of the living God and the Savior of the world. Everything changed at that moment. The Spirit in the room was undeniable. It seemed everyone was touched. “The Comforter … beareth record of the Father and of the Son.”I am so grateful I summoned the courage to bear my testimony."
  2022,"10",/general-conference/2022/10/55stevenson,Elder Gary E. Stevenson,68,"When a moment like this comes, grab it and embrace it. You will feel the warmth of the Comforter inside you when you do."
  2022,"10",/general-conference/2022/10/55stevenson,Elder Gary E. Stevenson,69,"I offer my testimony and witness to you—God is our Heavenly Father, Jesus Christ lives, and The Church of Jesus Christ of Latter-day Saints is God’s Church on the earth today led by our dear prophet, President Russell M. Nelson. In the name of Jesus Christ, amen."
